There are no aggravating factors. There are no relieving factors. Associated symptoms include cough, nasal congestion, post-nasal drainage, sinus pressure and sore throat. Pertinent negatives include chills, dyspnea, dyspnea on exertion, epistaxis, fatigue, fever, heartburn, hemoptysis, hoarseness, night sweats, pleuritic pain, rhinitis, weight loss and wheezing. The patient has a history of asthma. The patient does not have a history of allergies.
